## Defects — Risk & Decision Trace (audit objective 6)

### D14. Critical TBDs not flagged as blockers

Nine `_TBD_` markers exist:

- product.md:14 — "개발사: _TBD (파트너사 결정 미결)" — fundamental ownership ambiguity.
- structure.md:282 — "JWT 토큰 (공공기관 SSO 연동 _TBD)" — affects auth design.
- tech.md:143 — "Cross-Encoder 재순위화 _TBD".
- tech.md:203 — "GPU: A100/H100 _TBD" — bill-of-materials critical.
- tech.md:269 — "프라이빗 레지스트리 _TBD" — deployment-blocking.
- tech.md:416 — "AES-256 (저장, _TBD)" — security gate that section 9.4 (PISA) explicitly requires.
- tech.md:523 — "EXAONE 3.5 업그레이드 프로세스 _TBD".
- tech.md:553 — "EXAONE 3.5 문서 _TBD (LG AI 협력 후 공개)".
- tech.md:582 — "EXAONE 3.5 LG 기술 협력 확인 _TBD".

None of these are listed in §10 (product.md) or §13 (tech.md) risk tables as blockers requiring resolution before SPEC-AX-001 kickoff. A Day-1 engineer cannot tell which TBDs are blocking versus deferred.

Required fix: Add a "Decisions pending before SPEC-AX-001" section enumerating each TBD with owner and resolution criterion.

### D15. PoC vs Phase 1 KPI conflation

product.md §6.1 declares "**Go-Live 준비**: 안전보건 항목 완전 자동화 | 실제 PoC 배포 및 운영" as a PoC-phase success metric. But interview.md frames the safety-health work as a PoC (proof-of-concept), not production go-live. Calling PoC completion "Go-Live" overstates commitment and is hand-wavy.

Required fix: Clarify whether PoC ends in (a) a demo deliverable, (b) a pilot deployment to KEPCO E&C, or (c) full production go-live. Currently §6.1 implies all three.

