## Defects — Strategic Coherence (audit objective 7)

### D16. Self-hosted LLM + 망분리 + 한국어 stack — assumption depth not surfaced

The "Anchor → Platform" thesis rests on:

1. EXAONE 3.5 yielding good Korean-language report draft quality (assumption).
2. Qwen2-VL handling HWP page images well enough that hwp-converter need not be perfect (assumption).
3. Public agencies tolerating GPU procurement burden (A100/H100) on-prem.

None of these are surfaced as load-bearing assumptions. The "iroum-ax 포지셔닝" claim (product.md:287) of being like Linear / Notion / Figma is rhetorical — Linear / Notion / Figma are SaaS plays with cloud-native distribution, whereas iroum-ax explicitly targets on-prem self-hosting. The analogy contradicts the deployment model.

Required fix: Add explicit assumption list. Remove or restate the Linear/Notion/Figma analogy with caveat (these are horizontal cloud SaaS; iroum-ax is vertical on-prem — the only borrowed pattern is "anchor customer → platform").

### D17. GTM tension not addressed: Anchor → Platform timing

Interview line 132 originally suggested a "1차 12개월" anchor lock-in, then platform expansion. product.md replaces this with phase-labels (Phase 1/2/3) and quietly drops the 12-month commitment. This may be intentional (audit objective 4 forbids time predictions), but the absence of any pacing language leaves ambiguity: does Phase 2 begin only after KEPCO E&C signs renewal? After PoC technical acceptance? The strategic gate is undefined.

Required fix: Define the entry gate to each phase in evidence-based terms (e.g., "Phase 2 begins when KEPCO E&C accepts the safety-health draft against the 평가편람 with documented PoC report").

